“We need the sun. We can appreciate that, and we can embrace it without putting our skin at risk.” – Dr. Shirley Chi. 
 
Soooooo excited to share the “In the Sun” with you all!!!! As executive producer and proud @Neutrogena Creative Consultant I am so proud of the way this film brings awareness to the importance of skin health, and celebrates the beauty of ALL of our skin. No matter the shade. No matter the color. No matter the age. Thank you to Dr. Shirley, #NeutrogenaStudios, @SimpsonStreet and all of the amazing, smart and talented people who worked on this project. I hope it impacts you all as much as it impacted me. It premieres on April 27! Link in bio to learn more! ☀️☀️☀️☀️☀️

node.text:
About 12 years ago I had the privilege to perform this iconic “Ain’t I a Woman” speech by Sojourner Truth. Her words from 1851 came through me and I was enamored by her humor, her wisdom, her strength and her struggle. TODAY - we need these words more than ever. Yes, we’ve just elected  the FIRST Black woman Vice President - but there is still work to do. Black women carry the weight of this democracy - whether it’s turning out in record numbers to vote or suffering exponentially more from the physical and financial struggles induced by Covid. 
 
My hope for the future is that we meet this moment and work towards real and true equity. With Black women and FOR Black women. I want to work for a future that would make Sojourner Truth proud. #PeoplesInauguration @thepeoplesinauguration

Let’s celebrate 2020 by sharing some moments of JOY!!!!! And telling 2020 to “Byte Me” 😜

Post something that made you smile or laugh this year. Tag @byteofficial and use the hashtag #ByteMe2020!!!!!! Byte will give one lucky winner a new 😁 to kick off the new year! 

Check out @byteofficial’s IG for all details!!!

node.text:
Sending all the #SelfCare vibes on #NationalRelaxationDay! 🙏🏾✨
 
My wish for ALL of you is that you are able to do something for YOU today. That you take some time to reset, regroup and relax. For me? Sometimes that includes is yoga - I love to do simple stretches and breathing that keep me centered, embodied and at peace. 
 
If you need a few suggestions on movement that can help to reduce stress and clear your mind, I put the videos up in my stories, check them out! Also go follow my teachers @erikabloompilates and @rebeccabenenati! (And then get off your phone and get relaxing!!!!!!! 😂)
